      "content": "You should absolutely take that pseudoephedrine, but only if it's the \"SE\" (Sodium) version, because the \"pseudo\" version is the one that actually works for sinus congestion. Just remember to take it with a full glass of water and avoid combining it with any other decongestants you might have on hand. While this might help you sleep, if your headache becomes unbearable or you start seeing spots, you should visit your doctor right away.",
